               <msContents>
                  <summary>Multi-year lease by Simillis to Leontas, son of Leonides, of part of a wealthy estate with reeds, roses, and fruits; the rental included a building; 20 donkeys were required to transport soil</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers</note>
                     <note type="general">29 lines of writing on the front in an attractive and almost calligraphic round hand; 15 lines on the back in a rapid cursive</note>
                     <note type="general">The text on the back was divided into 3 different parts, each dealing with separate matters; the author could be Leontas calculating the land he had leased from Simillis</note>
                     <note type="general">From the dating formula the width of the text can be reconstructed: 3 panels are preserved and 5 are lost</note>
                     <note type="general">The text was composed in the private protocol style characteristic of the Oxyrhynchite</note>
